The article is a proclamation by President Barack Obama declaring June 16, 2013, as Father's Day in the United States. The proclamation recognizes the hard work and dedication of fathers in raising their children and emphasizes the importance of their role as loving parents. The President acknowledges the commitment of fathers in various aspects of their children's lives, such as attending school events, helping with homework, and instilling life lessons. The proclamation also highlights the significance of mentors, tutors, and foster dads in providing fatherly support to young people in need. President Obama encourages the nation to support and appreciate fathers, and directs government officials to display the flag on all government buildings on Father's Day.